# S05-T07: Touch-Safe Controls

## Objective
Provide a small library of touch-safe primitives: Button, IconButton, Toggle, Slider, Select.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/shared/ui/` houses primitives.
- All targets ≥ 48×48px (preferred 56×56).
- No hover-only state — all interactions surfaced via touch.
- Disabled state visually distinct (low-opacity gray-green per UI_REGULATION).
- Touch feedback: 1px border brightens within 50ms on press.

## Steps
1. Implement `<Button>` (variants: primary, alert, ghost).
2. Implement `<IconButton>` (square, min 48×48).
3. Implement `<Toggle>`, `<Slider>`, `<Select>` (basic, accessible).
4. Document each primitive in storybook-free MDX (deferred to S06).

## Invariants
- No JS-driven hover effects.
- Active/press visual response within one frame.
- All controls keyboard-accessible (focus ring per UI_REGULATION cyan).
